<h1>K&amp;N Replacement Automotive Air Filters</h1>
  <table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" width="980">
    <tr>
      <td><table width="782" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" align="center">
    <tr>
      <td width="386"><p>&nbsp;<br/></p><p><strong>Designed to Increase Horsepower &amp; Acceleration<br />
          K&amp;N Million Mile Limited Warranty<sup>&reg;</sup><br />
          Washable and Reusable</strong><br />
          <ul>
            <li>Will <u>NOT</u> Void 
            Vehicle Warranty</li>
          <li>Lasts up to 50,000 
            miles before cleaning is required depending on driving conditions</li>
          <li>Emissions Legal in all 50 US States.</li>
          <li>Economical, a K&amp;N Air Filter Will
            Last the Life of Your Automobile, Motorcycle, or ATV</li>
          <li>Works with Vehicle Electronics</li>
          <li>Environmentally Friendly</li>
</ul></p></td>
        <td width="10"></td>
      <td width="386"><p align="center"><img alt="K&amp;N Air Filters - Designed to Increase Horsepower &amp; Acceleration" height="125" src="images/air_filter_boxes160w.jpg" width="160" /></p>
      <hr/><p style="text-align:center; margin:0;"><a class="xlg" href="search/appsearch.aspx"><strong>Search Here to Find a K&amp;N 
        Filter<br/>for Your Vehicle!</strong></a></p><hr/>
        <p style="text-align:center; margin:0;"><a class="xlg" href="search/cross_reference.aspx"><strong>Use Our Cross Reference Guide if You Know a Manufacturer's Part Number!</strong></a>
        <hr/></p></td>
    </tr>

<p>
<DIV style="float: left; width: 214px; height: 333px; padding-left: 8px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 4px">
<CENTER>
<img border="0" src="images/2cfilter.jpg" width="161" height="160" alt="K&amp;N High-Flow Air Filter" /><br />
K&amp;N Automotive Panel Air Filter
<br /><br />
<img border="0" src="images/PowerSports/KN-PS-Air-Filter-Group.jpg" width="160" height="110" alt="K&amp;N Motorcycle and ATV Air Filters" /><br />
K&amp;N Motorcycle and ATV Air Filters
</CENTER>
</DIV>
<strong>The Original High-Flow Air Filter</strong><br />
      Since 1969 K&amp;N Engineering has been designing, manufacturing, and enhancing High-Flow Air Filters for the automotive and motorcycle enthusiast interested in maximizing horsepower and acceleration.&nbsp; Since our humble beginnings we have designed and manufactured over 2,400 High-Flow Air Filters to fit most modern passenger vehicles and over 500 High-Flow <a href="kits.htm">Air Intake Systems</a> to fit vehicles driven by enthusiast minded drivers.&nbsp; We not only have more applications than any other manufacturer of similar product, we invented the High-Flow category and the High-Flow Technology that supports it.&nbsp; K&amp;N also makes thousands of <a href="performance_accessories.htm">racing and specialty</a> type air filters and is the #1 Filter in NASCAR<sup>&reg;</sup>.</p>
<p>
<DIV style="float: right; width: 143px; height: 219px; padding-right: 8px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 4px">
<CENTER>
<img border="0" src="images/KNNorm.jpg" width="128" height="200" alt="K&amp;N Motorcycle Racing" />
</CENTER>
</DIV>
The K&amp;N FilterCharger<sup>&reg;</sup> air filter is designed to achieve high, virtually unrestricted air flow while maintaining filtration levels critical to ensure long engine life.&nbsp; Our automotive OE (original equipment) replacement air filters generally add 1-4 horsepower. The secret to our success lies in the unique characteristics of our filter medium that was originally developed by K&amp;N all those years ago in the dust, sweat and tears of desert motocross racing.&nbsp; We just wanted to win races and stumbled on a cotton filtration technology destined to be great.&nbsp; Our high flow cotton gauze air filter is washable, reusable and built to last for the life of an automotive or motorcycle engine.&nbsp; K&amp;N air filters consist of four to six sheets of cotton gauze layered between two sheets of aluminum wire mesh.&nbsp; This media is then pleated and oiled to enhance its filtering capabilities and overall performance.&nbsp;  K&amp;N Air Filters were created for an  environment requiring maximum horsepower and enhanced acceleration in addition to protection from the dirt and dust of off-road racing.&nbsp; The result is an air filter that allows dramatically more air into an engine, is washable and reusable, and will protect your engine for the life of your vehicle.</p>

      <p><strong>Engine Protection, Filtration</strong><br />
Anyone can flow more air.&nbsp; The trick is to flow more air safely.&nbsp; In 
our opinion we hit the sweet spot &#8211; an optimal blend of high air flow, 
filtration efficiency, durability and dust capacity.&nbsp; We take filtration 
seriously.&nbsp; K&amp;N Air Filter media has been tested both in-house and by 
independent labs using the ISO5011 test developed by the Society of Automotive 
Engineers.&nbsp; In addition we test many of our filters both in and out of the 
OE airbox ensuring proper fit and function.&nbsp; Our goal is to design filters 
with the maximum possible airflow achievable while providing guaranteed engine 
protection.</p>
<p>
<DIV style="float: left; width: 230px; height: 469px; padding-right: 8px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 4px">
<CENTER>
<img border="0" src="images/microfilter.jpg" width="201" height="180" />
<br /><br />
<a href="million/default.htm">
<img border="0" src="images/performance/Carlmillion.jpg" width="201" height="238" alt="Carl and his million mile Chevy truck with K&amp;N Air Filter installed." /></a>
<br />
<a class="nav2" href="million/default.htm">More on Carl's Million Mile Truck Here!</a>
</CENTER>
</DIV>
<strong>The Importance of Oil</strong><br />A K&amp;N Air Filter is made of 4 to 6 layers of cotton gauze sandwiched between two epoxy-coated aluminum wire screens.&nbsp; The cotton is treated with a specially 
formulated grade of oil causing tackiness throughout the cotton&#8217;s microscopic 
strands.&nbsp; The nature of the cotton allows high volumes of airflow, and when 
combined with the tackiness of the oil creates a powerful filtering media that 
ensures engine protection.&nbsp; In contrast, most other media can not maintain 
the same balance of airflow and filtration throughout the filter's life without 
sacrificing one or the other.&nbsp; With a K&amp;N Air Filter, there is no 
sacrifice.</p>
<p>
<DIV style="float: right; width: 245px; height: 170px; padding-right: 8px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 4px">
<CENTER>
<img border="0" src="images/performance/lab3.jpg" width="224" height="150" alt="K&amp;N Laboratory" /><br />
</CENTER>
</DIV>
<strong>Testing &#8211; Laboratory and Real World</strong><br />
K&amp;N uses independent laboratories to help ensure that our products meet or 
exceed your high performance and high filtration demands.&nbsp; Better yet, we conduct 
our own testing at our own state-of-the-art in-house testing laboratory.&nbsp; 
For more information on K&amp;N air filters and testing go to the
      <a href="facts.htm">K&amp;N Technical Learning Center</a> 
      area.&nbsp; K&amp;N&#8217;s dedication to providing a first-class air filter can 
      also be seen outside the testing laboratory. Consider that K&amp;N has sold 
      more than 20 million air filters since 1969. One such filter was put in 
      the airbox of a three-quarter ton Chevy pickup and driven more than one 
      million miles by Carl Judice of New Iberia, Louisiana. Carl points out 
      that he has never rebuilt the engine, nor removed the cylinder head from 
      his trusty pickup truck. Real world testing and customer satisfaction 
      doesn&#8217;t get any better than that. <a href="million/default.htm">Click here</a> 
      for more information on Carl and his million mile truck.
&nbsp;</p>
      <p><strong>Never Replace Your Air Filter Again</strong><br />Handmade in the USA and in the United Kingdom using only the finest materials, 
K&amp;N OE Replacement Air Filters are washable and reusable.&nbsp; Regardless 
of what you&#8217;ve heard, it&#8217;s almost impossible to wash your K&amp;N Air Filter too 
much.&nbsp; Inside our testing laboratory, we have washed and re-oiled one K&amp;N 
Air Filter more than 100 times and it still performs up to specification.&nbsp; 
Depending on your driving conditions, we recommend cleaning your air filter every 
50,000 miles.&nbsp; To clean and re-oil, purchase our filter
<a href="clningacc.htm">Recharger</a><sup>&reg;</sup> <a href="clningacc.htm">
service kit</a> and follow the easy instructions.</p>
<p>
<DIV style="float: right; width: 218px; height: 436px; padding-right: 8px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 4px">
<CENTER>
<img border="0" src="images/performance/KNGasPump.gif" width="204" height="222" alt="K&amp;N Air Filters and Fuel Economy" /><br />
<img border="0" src="images/performance/Million-Mile-200px.gif" width="195" height="195" alt="K&amp;N Million Mile Limited Warranty" />
</CENTER>
</DIV>
<strong>Fuel Economy</strong><br />
Fuel economy testing and mileage claims are a tricky business. Just ask the EPA, 
whose website states, &#8220;EPA&#8217;s fuel economy estimates are designed to allow 
consumers to comparison shop.&nbsp; Your fuel economy will almost certainly vary 
from EPA&#8217;s fuel economy rating.&nbsp; This is based on a number of factors, such 
as weather, road conditions, your driving and maintenance habits, and your use 
of air conditioning.&#8221;&nbsp; A lot of 
exaggerated claims are made in the marketplace by products claiming to improve 
gas mileage.&nbsp; K&amp;N makes no general fuel economy claims, however we encourage you 
to try our air filter for yourself.&nbsp; Keeping air filter restriction as low as 
possible can be an important tool, among others, for maintaining high mileage.&nbsp; For more info 
read what some of our users have to say on the <a href="register/feedback.aspx">K&amp;N 
testimonials page</a>.</p>
<p><strong>K&amp;N Million Mile Limited Warranty<sup>&reg;</sup> and Consumer Protection Pledge</strong><br />K&amp;N warrants its street vehicle OE Replacement Air Filters for one million miles. When used 
properly and found to be defective, return your filter and the receipt from 
purchase and K&amp;N will replace it free of charge. K&amp;N&#8217;s Consumer Protection Plan 
goes one step further than its <a href="warranty.htm">Million Mile Warranty</a>. The performance 
aftermarket has, at times, been plagued by car manufacturers and automotive 
dealers that may attempt to discourage you from customizing your vehicle. They 
prefer you buy OE parts and not modify your car or truck and have even been 
known to void their own manufacturer&#8217;s warranty due to vehicle modification. 
That sounds un-American to us, which is why K&amp;N and the Magnuson-Moss Warranty 
Act (<a href="warrantyletter.htm">more information here</a>) 
protect consumers from such denied warranty claims.&nbsp; When you buy an OE 
replacement K&amp;N High-Flow Air Filter or High-Flow Air Intake System you can be 
confident your vehicle&#8217;s warranty will remain in effect.&nbsp; If you experience a 
difficult dealership, K&amp;N will resolve the issue so you won&#8217;t have to. The 
following summarizes the K&amp;N Consumer Protection Pledge:</p>
<p><strong>K&amp;N pledges to our customers that they will not be taken advantage of and 
charged for a repair due to a dealership warranty denial blamed on the presence 
of a K&amp;N product..</strong></p>
<p>See our <a href="maf/massairpledge.htm">pledge page</a> for more details.
<br /><br />
We believe K&amp;N makes <strong>The World&#8217;s Best Air Filter</strong> and we stand behind that claim 
100 percent.</p>
